description:
Our place is a 20 min DIRECT subway ride to Manhattan.The metro station is around the corner and our home is in the Brooklyn historic/landmark brownstone district. We love it and hope you would too-a cozy 1 bedroom+1 bathroom apt with high-end stainless steel appliances,dishwasher,gas range,hardwood floors,huge bathroom,gorgeous design+high speed internet.A great supermarket 4 min walk from us.
Great for couples,solo adventurers,business travelers,families with or without kids-young or grown;)

This is a beautiful separate apartment comprising of the entire floor of our beautiful brownstone house.  We have maintained the historic charm of the home while upgrading it with gorgeous high-end stainless steel appliances, fixtures, and tiles.  We love our home and hope you would, too

The maximum amount of people that can fit in the apartment is 4 and the space is ideal for a travelling family who seeks the comforts of being home while on a trip.

Below is a detailed breakdown of the area configuration:

BEDROOM: 1 queen size bed (size of mattress is 60/80 inches or 152cm/203cm) with a brand new high quality 12'' (30cm)  memory foam mattress; ceiling fan, Mitsubishi wall airconditioner, dresser with mirror, original fireplace (non-working); makeup mirror; iron with ironing board; full size wall mirror; an entire wall with bookshelves; original crown moldings.

Guests will be provided with pillows, bed linens, towels, as well as soap, shampoo and conditioner.

LIVING ROOM: 1 sofa which opens to FULL SIZE bed (54/75 inches which is 137cm/190cm) with a memory foam mattress for comfortable sleeping; 40'' Samsung SmartTV with access to netflix; wifi internet; window airconditioner; 2 side tables

KITCHEN: round dining table for 4; Verona 24'' Italian stainless steel gas range; 18 inch Bosch dishwasher; Panasonic stainless steel microwave; stainless steel kettle; stainless steel toaster; stainless steel cooking pots and pans; TEFAL pan; plates; utensils; glasses; Bodum Chambord French Press Coffee Maker; KitchenAid Kettle.

BATHROOM: bathtub; rain shower head; hair dryer; first aid kit, toilet paper.

The space comprises of the entire floor of our parlor level and is set up as its own apartment with its own separate entrance.

We are available to help if anything comes up as we live here

The area is an up-and coming area and we absolutely love our neighborhood and hope that everyone will see the beauty in it!

This is not an all white homogeneous area.  The neighborhood consists of people of all colors and all faiths.

If you are looking for an all white people neighborhood, please do not rent our apartment!

Our place is part of a huge historic district and the houses are absolutely gorgeous.

It takes about 20 minutes to get to Manhattan with the local C train.  The Kingston-Throop station is located around the corner and is a direct ride to Manhattan. It takes about 4 minutes to walk to the subway station.

We are looking for guests who would appreciate the beauty of our home.

Our home is NOT A PARTY ZONE and we do not appreciate guests who are looking for a place to throw a party or a big event

NO SMOKING!

hosts.about:
We are the Cohen Family and we would love to welcome you at our modest home! We used to live in mid-town Manhattan, in the concrete jungle, and decided to move to Brownstone Brooklyn a couple of years ago.  We are SO happy we made that choice! We love living in Brooklyn where everyone has a smile on their face and greets you on the street.  There is a true sense of community and the houses are absolutely gorgeous, carrying the typical NYC brownstone heart everyone has seen in the movies....
We love to travel and to be with our friends and family and we think that there is nothing like a good laugh with a good company of friends and family!
We don't take ourselves too seriously as we have learned that life is both too short and full of surprises and one can never plan too much - one never knows what the next day will bring, so we should greet each day with a smile!
We look forward to welcoming you at our home!
